==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''dozen'''|'''[[dozen]] '''when used attributive,''' [[dozens]] '''otherwise}}

#''(countable)'' A [[set]] of [[twelve]].
#:''Can I have a dozen eggs, please?'' 
#:''There shouldn't be more than two dozen Christmas cards left to write.''
#:''Pack the shirts in dozens, please.''
#''(As plural only, always followed by ''[[of]]'')'' '''Dozens of''': A [[large]], [[unspecified]] [[number]] of; [[many]].
#:''There must have been dozens of examples just on the first page.''
#An old English measure of [[ore]] containg 12 [[hundredweight]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1957''': The dozen as a measure for iron ore remained almost completely constant at 12 cwts. during the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries. &mdash; H.R. Schubert, ''History of the British Iron and Steel Industry'', p. 139.

====Derived terms====
*[[baker's dozen]]<!-- possibly bakers' dozen also/instead -->
*[[cheaper by the dozen]]

